The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 August is 65,395 (7,537.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 August, there were 2,611 new confirmed cases (300.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 August, there were 2,551 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 2% (60 extra cases).
